[Like Ep. 388 evidently a first letter to Erasmus, since his departure from England in May 1515. It was sent to Pace, who was in Switzerland (Ep. 388. 94 n.), to be forwarded, but failed to reach Erasmus ; and Ammonius

therefore sent another copy of it in June, when Erasmus had returned to the ¹'

Netherlands (Epp. 427 and 429). The mouth-date given is incorrect in view of the mention of the Princess Mary's birth (1. 59 11.). It can be rectified easily in the way suggested in the text ; that Ammonius should have calculated for the leap-year without reckoning for the bissextile day is less likely]
